      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) represents a mechanically sound example of the marque's transition to water-cooling. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, the engine provides a robust torque curve and 320 hp delivered through a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance is documented, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The suspension geometry remains precise with upgraded Bilstein B6 dampers and replaced lower control arms, maintaining the communicative feedback inherent to the 996 chassis. While the exterior shows minor signs of spirited road use, the drivetrain and hydraulic steering rack are in excellent sync, offering a pure analog driving experience.",
